The birth of a baby is always special, but early this morning a little girl was born who has a special significance to an entire nation.

With the arrival of Jennalyn Sentino the Philippines has become only the 12th country in the world to have a population of more than 100million people.

She was one of 100 babies born in state-run hospitals all over the sprawling archipelago who were given the symbolic designation of '100,000,000th baby'.

